    list AqmCfg {
      description "Additional definitions from MOM:min/max-elements:0/32; Automatic queue management configuration selection profile. Instances AqmCfg=Default_conversational_media instance, Default_application_signaling, and Default_other are created automatically when parent MO instance is created, unless created manually in same transaction. DrbUpUeCfg::aqmCfgRef is automatically set to following MO instance: - AqmCfg=Default_conversational_media instance, if DrbUpUeCfg instance is created under parent DrbUp=Default_conversational_media instance. - AqmCfg=Default_application_signaling, if DrbUpUeCfg instance is created under parent DrbUp=Default_application_signaling instance. - AqmCfg=Default_other, if DrbUpUeCfg instance is created under other parent Drb instance. Unless manually set to refer to another MO instance. Only applicable when GNBDUFunction::altDepHServAdapUPProfEnabled is true. Precondition: Instances AqmCfg=Default_application_signaling, Default_conversational_media, and Default_other can only be created in same transaction as parent MO instance and cannot be deleted unless parent MO instance is deleted. Other instances can be created and deleted manually. Maximum 29 AqmCfg instances, with RDN different from Default_application_signaling, Default_conversational_media, or Default_other can be created under same parent MO instance.";
